-- Russian Billionaires Potanin, Mamut Merge Internet Assets
-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 2013-03-29T15:33:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-29/russian-billionaires-potanin-mamut-merge-internet-assets.html
Russian billionaires  Vladimir Potanin  and  Alexander Mamut  merged their online-media assets to
create Russia’s third-largest Internet group by audience.  Potanin’s Rambler-Afisha and Mamut’s SUP Media are
combining in a merger of equals and will have a total audience
of 35 million unique monthly visitors, the companies said in a
 statement  on the SUP Media website.  SUP Media owns LiveJournal.com, a social media platform
with user-generated content, and online newspaper Gazeta.ru,
according to the website. Potanin’s Internet assets include
search engine Rambler.ru, news website Lenta.ru and Afisha
entertainment and leisure media.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Khrennikov in Moscow at 
 ikhrennikov@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
